make it so can read in a pdf adventure and run that

more of a human command line

Instead of hardcoding OSE rules, store them in DB and let tools reference them:
    •    class_progression tables (xp thresholds, thac0, saves, spell slots)
    •    equipment tables (price, weight, tags)
    •    monster minimal stats (HD, AC, morale, treasure type)
    •    services table for towns
    •    pc_apply_class_tables(pc_id) (pull exact numbers)
    •    market_seed_ose_basic()
    •    seed_monsters_from_refs(...) (if your refs index is good)

    •    campaign_list()
    •    campaign_create(name)
    •    campaign_switch(name)
    •    campaign_backup() (copy to timestamped file)
    •    campaign_export_json() / campaign_import_json()

    •    dungeon_turn(pc_id, dungeon_id):
      •    tick light
      •    tick time
      •    encounter check
      •    resource tick (rations every N turns)
      •    returns “what happens next” suggestions
    •    travel_day(party_ids, hex_from, hex_to):
      •    weather
      •    encounter check (by hex biome + danger)
      •    fatigue / rations
      •    updates location/time

    •    party_create(name)
    •    party_add_pc(party_id, pc_id)
    •    party_add_hireling(party_id, hireling_id)
    •    party_status(party_id) (HP, light, encumbrance summary)
    •    party_location_set(party_id, hex_key, site_id=None)
    •    log_event(text, tags=[...])
    •    log_last(n=20)
    •    session_recap() (summarize last N entries)
    •    bookmark(name) (save state points)

